results.name: Decimal expansion of arccos(1/phi), where phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 (the golden ratio).
comment: Every cyclic quadrilateral all of whose angles are greater than arccos((sqrt(5)-1)/2) admits a 3 × 1 grid dissection into three cyclic quadrilaterals [Thm. 2.3 in Choi et al. p. 2]. - _Michel Marcus_, Aug 13 2019
link: Erica Choi, Dan Ismailescu, Jiho Lee, Joonsoo Lee, Grid dissections of tangential quadrilaterals, arXiv:1908.02251 [math.MG], 2019.
